     Dec. 28 (Bloomberg)--  Iran â€™s Energy Ministry plans to offer
about $243 million of participation bonds denominated in Iranian
rials to fund the completion of its hydroelectric plants, the
 Islamic Republic News Agency  reported yesterday.  Tehran-based Bank Sepah will sell the bonds from Dec. 31,
and interest on the debt will be paid on a quarterly basis, the
